        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:34PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Milford, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sherman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
